==English==

===Etymology===
German ''adal'' (noble) + ''berht'' (bright); {{ang}} ''Aeþelbeorht''. Became very popular in 19th century England due to Queen Victoria's consort Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha

===Proper noun===
'''Albert'''

# A [[male]] [[given name]].  Diminutives: [[Al]], [[Bert]], [[Bertie]].

